    EMERGENCY WAKE PROTOCOL INITIATED...
    CRYOSLEEP POD 7 - SYSTEMS OPERATOR
    DATE: UNKNOWN
    LOCATION: UNKNOWN

    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    You wake to the sound of alarms. Red emergency lights pulse through
    the darkness of the airlock chamber. The last thing you remember is
    entering cryosleep as the Odyssey departed for the Kepler system.

    Something has gone terribly wrong.

    The ship's main AI, ARIA, is offline. Most of the crew remains in
    cryosleep. The emergency terminal in front of you flickers to life:

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  ARIA EMERGENCY BACKUP v0.7                                    │
    │  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────  │
    │                                                                 │
    │  CRITICAL ALERT: Multiple system failures detected             │
    │  CREW STATUS: 23/24 in cryosleep                               │
    │  SHIP STATUS: Life support NOMINAL, all other systems OFFLINE  │
    │                                                                 │
    │  You are the only crew member with terminal access clearance.  │
    │  You must navigate the ship's computer systems to restore      │
    │  functionality before life support fails.                      │
    │                                                                 │
    │  Begin by reading your mission briefing:  cat .mission         │
    │                                                                 │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    HELPFUL COMMANDS:
    • ls           - List files in current location
    • ls -la       - List ALL files (including hidden ones starting with .)
    • cat <file>   - Read a file's contents
    • cd <dir>     - Move to a different directory
    • pwd          - Show your current location
    • clear        - Clear the terminal screen

